# Frontend Feature Conventions

## Feature Structure

Every feature lives in `apps/web/src/features/<feature-name>/`:

```
features/<name>/
  index.tsx              # Page component (default export)
  components/            # Feature-specific components
    <name>-table.tsx
    <name>-columns.tsx
    <name>-dialogs.tsx
    <name>-action-dialog.tsx
    <name>-delete-dialog.tsx
    <name>-provider.tsx
    <name>-primary-buttons.tsx
  data/
    schema.ts            # Types derived from API (AppRouterClient)
  hooks/                 # Feature-specific hooks (optional)
```

## Routing

TanStack Router file-based routes. Route files are thin wrappers:

```tsx
// routes/_authenticated/<name>/index.tsx
import { createFileRoute } from "@tanstack/react-router";
import { z } from "zod";
import { Feature } from "@/features/<name>";

const searchSchema = z.object({
  page: z.number().optional().default(1),
  // filters...
});

export const Route = createFileRoute("/_authenticated/<name>/")({
  validateSearch: searchSchema,
  component: Feature,
});
```

## Data Fetching (oRPC + TanStack Query)

```tsx
import { useQuery, useMutation, useQueryClient } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { orpc } from "@/lib/orpc";

// Read
const { data, isLoading } = useQuery(orpc.<router>.<procedure>.queryOptions());

// With input
const { data } = useQuery(orpc.<router>.get.queryOptions({ input: { id } }));

// Mutation + invalidation
const queryClient = useQueryClient();
const mutation = useMutation(
  orpc.<router>.create.mutationOptions({
    onSuccess: () => {
      queryClient.invalidateQueries(orpc.<router>.list.queryOptions());
      toast.success("Created successfully");
    },
  })
);
```

## UI Imports

- **Primitives**: `@workspace/ui/components/<name>` (Button, Dialog, Field, Input, Select, Table, Card, Badge, etc.)
- **Empty state**: `@workspace/ui/components/empty` (Empty, EmptyHeader, EmptyMedia, EmptyTitle, EmptyDescription, EmptyContent)
- **Utilities**: `cn` from `@workspace/ui/lib/utils`
- **App layout**: `@/components/layout/content-layout`
- **Long text**: `@/components/long-text` (LongText — truncates with tooltip/popover on overflow)
- **Data table**: `@/components/data-table` (DataTableToolbar, DataTablePagination)
- **Confirm dialog**: `@/components/confirm-dialog`
- **Icons**: `lucide-react`

## Page Component Pattern

```tsx
import { ContentLayout } from "@/components/layout/content-layout";
import { Loader } from "@/components/loader";

export default function FeaturePage() {
  const { data, isLoading } = useQuery(orpc.<router>.list.queryOptions());

  if (isLoading) return <Loader />;

  return (
    <ContentLayout title="Feature Name">
      <FeatureProvider>
        <FeaturePrimaryButtons />
        <FeatureTable data={data ?? []} />
        <FeatureDialogs />
      </FeatureProvider>
    </ContentLayout>
  );
}
```

## Forms (TanStack Form + Zod)

```tsx
import { useForm } from "@tanstack/react-form";
import { Field, FieldLabel, FieldError, FieldGroup } from "@workspace/ui/components/field";
import { Input } from "@workspace/ui/components/input";
import { Button } from "@workspace/ui/components/button";

const form = useForm({
  defaultValues: { name: "", email: "" },
  validators: { onSubmit: formSchema },
  onSubmit: async ({ value }) => {
    await mutation.mutateAsync(value);
  },
});
```

## Dialog / Modal Pattern

Use Provider + `useDialogState` hook to control open state:

```tsx
// Provider manages: open state ("add" | "edit" | "delete" | null), currentRow
// Dialogs mount inside Provider, read state via context
// Actions dispatch: setOpen("add"), setOpen("edit"), setOpen(null)
```

## Tables (TanStack Table)

- Define columns in `<name>-columns.tsx` with `ColumnDef<T>[]`
- Use `useReactTable` + `Table` primitives from `@workspace/ui/components/table`
- Sync pagination/filters to URL via `useTableUrlState` hook
- Wrap long text cells (titles, filenames) with `<LongText>` from `@/components/long-text`
- Use `<Empty>` from `@workspace/ui/components/empty` for empty table states instead of plain text
```

## State Management

- **Server state**: TanStack Query (primary)
- **Local UI state**: React Context + useState (dialogs, selections)
- **Complex client-only state**: zustand (when React Context becomes unwieldy)
- **Toasts**: `sonner` via `toast.success()` / `toast.error()`

## Type Derivation

Derive types from the API client, not manual interfaces:

```tsx
// data/schema.ts
import type { AppRouterClient } from "@/lib/orpc";
type Employee = Awaited<ReturnType<AppRouterClient["employee"]["list"]>>[number];
```
